WEBVTT

00:01.968 --> 00:03.369
        [ Remote clicks ]

00:03.371 --> 00:05.004
     [ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.475 --> 00:10.409
 � I don't care what you say! �

00:11.679 --> 00:13.679
   � I'm gonna do what I want
           all day! �

00:13.681 --> 00:16.315
  � I'm the king of the world!
  I'm the king of the world! �

00:16.317 --> 00:18.217
   � I'm the king of the world!
   I'm the king of the world! �

00:18.219 --> 00:22.888
  � I'm the king of the world!
  I'm the king of the world! �

00:28.963 --> 00:33.032
                     ��

00:33.367 --> 00:35.134
           [ Giggles ]

00:39.306 --> 00:41.573
              Whoa.

00:41.575 --> 00:43.175
     Wow, Jeff.

00:43.177 --> 00:45.878
     You're really excited about
       seeing your grandma, huh?

00:45.880 --> 00:47.413
   Of course I am.

00:47.415 --> 00:50.516
She's pretty much the nicest,
most organized person I know.

00:50.518 --> 00:51.917
                 Ugh. Pfbt.

00:51.919 --> 00:53.819
              Old people candy
                tastes gross.

00:53.821 --> 00:55.888
             Just grab one more.

00:55.890 --> 00:59.024
     [ Indistinct talking ]

00:59.026 --> 01:01.260
         You promise you'll keep
            your cool this time?

01:01.262 --> 01:04.830
    She's my mom.
I know how to deal with her.

01:04.831 --> 01:06.331
           [ Slurps ]

01:06.333 --> 01:08.233
          [ Smooching ]

01:08.235 --> 01:09.835
            [ Ding ]

01:09.837 --> 01:11.103
              Ooh.

01:11.105 --> 01:12.371
       [ Piano flourish ]

01:12.373 --> 01:14.006
            [ Gasps ]

01:16.377 --> 01:17.609
             Piano.

01:17.611 --> 01:21.080
           [ Giggles ]

01:21.082 --> 01:23.515
           [ Humming ]

01:25.686 --> 01:26.885
          [ Cat yowls ]
              Aaah!

01:26.887 --> 01:28.087
            Oh. Aww.

01:28.089 --> 01:29.288
       Is this your piano?

01:29.290 --> 01:30.889
  What's your name, kitty cat?

01:30.891 --> 01:32.858
          [ Cat yowls ]
 Her name's Sassy.

01:32.860 --> 01:35.094
  And yours must be
      Get Lost.

01:35.096 --> 01:36.395
               [ Giggles ] No.

01:36.397 --> 01:38.464
               It's Clarence.
              What's your name?

01:38.466 --> 01:41.266
The name's Shake A Leg, and you
better be learning it quick.

01:41.268 --> 01:42.868
         You kind of talk funny.

01:42.870 --> 01:44.036
            Are you from Europe?

01:44.038 --> 01:45.604
    No.
           Can I touch your cat?

01:45.606 --> 01:47.473
       No.
                     Can I...

01:47.475 --> 01:49.141
              play your piano?

01:49.143 --> 01:50.309
Let me think about it.

01:50.311 --> 01:51.710
      No.
                   [ Giggles ]

01:51.712 --> 01:53.278
                    Wow.
        You have a lot of rules.

01:53.280 --> 01:55.080
             Like, at my school,
               the only person

01:55.082 --> 01:56.615
                who's allowed
             to touch the piano

01:56.617 --> 01:59.985
     is the music teacher 'cause
        me and my friend Sumo...

01:59.987 --> 02:01.487
             [ Belches quietly ]

02:01.489 --> 02:05.157
      ...we were musical chairs,
          but we sat on the keys

02:05.159 --> 02:07.292
               with our butts.

02:09.096 --> 02:10.329
          Can I play your piano?

02:10.330 --> 02:13.332
 Well, if you're not
gonna leave, I will.

02:13.334 --> 02:14.633
                   Cloris.

02:14.635 --> 02:15.901
               Like Clarence!

02:15.903 --> 02:18.003
  No. It's old name
  for an old woman.

02:18.005 --> 02:20.172
     Now scram!
I'm trying to finish my work!

02:20.174 --> 02:21.607
      You're knitting a sweater?

02:21.609 --> 02:23.809
            That's like the most
             grandma thing ever.

02:23.811 --> 02:25.410
 No, you bird brain.
      I'm cold!

02:25.412 --> 02:27.613
  These cheapskates
never turn on the heat!

02:27.615 --> 02:29.781
          But do you like candy?

02:29.783 --> 02:31.850
         Mm.

02:31.852 --> 02:33.519
           [ Singing ]

02:33.521 --> 02:34.987
   Hi, Grandma.
                        Ooh!

02:34.989 --> 02:36.455
                       Jeffrey!
   [ Panting ]

02:36.457 --> 02:38.824
                Oh, it's just
             so good to see you.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.826
           Hi, Rose.
                        Oh, Sue.

02:40.828 --> 02:42.928
              You smell so nice
                 this time.

02:42.930 --> 02:44.263
             Thank you for that.

02:44.265 --> 02:46.665
              Elanor Josephine.

02:46.667 --> 02:48.167
               You wore boots.

02:48.169 --> 02:50.335
               You know boots
             scuff the linoleum.

02:50.337 --> 02:52.304
I like wearing boots,
        Mom.

02:52.306 --> 02:54.206
            Together:
    Rules exist for a reason.

02:54.208 --> 02:55.974
   That's because we need 'em.

02:55.976 --> 02:57.276
         [ Both laugh ]

02:57.278 --> 02:59.044
               Let's put those
               in some water.

02:59.046 --> 03:00.045
         Deep breathing.

03:00.047 --> 03:01.446
 [ Inhales sharply ]

03:01.448 --> 03:02.447
      [ Sighs ]

03:02.449 --> 03:04.783
    We only want
   the nice ones.

03:04.785 --> 03:06.451
                   Mm-hmm.

03:08.789 --> 03:10.856
              Wow.

03:10.858 --> 03:12.357
Give me some space, kid.

03:12.359 --> 03:14.193
                 [ Giggles ]
             Your old-lady mouth

03:14.195 --> 03:16.962
             has to work so hard
             to chew that candy.

03:16.964 --> 03:19.231
    I haven't had
   candy in ages.

03:19.233 --> 03:21.800
Only thing they feed you
around here is garbage.

03:21.802 --> 03:23.168
          Is this your yearbook?

03:23.170 --> 03:25.170
Is that's a scrapbook, son.

03:25.172 --> 03:28.407
These old bones have seen
100 many days gone by.

03:28.409 --> 03:29.575
                I signed it!

03:29.577 --> 03:32.244
        I was sick when everyone
          was signing yearbooks.

03:32.246 --> 03:35.714
         I was gonna draw a bear
         and sign it "Bearance."

03:35.716 --> 03:36.982
                    See?

03:36.984 --> 03:38.350
      [ Sighs ]

03:38.352 --> 03:40.385
     Is this you at Bendle Park?

03:40.387 --> 03:44.089
   Yeah, that's me
and [Chuckles] Rosie.

03:44.091 --> 03:45.691
It was a different time.

03:45.693 --> 03:48.327
   Life was rich,
and it was an adventure.

03:48.329 --> 03:51.997
I'd bury my treasure,
and she'd come 'round and snoop.

03:51.999 --> 03:53.832
Ah, but that's all history.

03:53.834 --> 03:55.601
            Clarence!
         There you are!

03:55.603 --> 03:59.071
And I totally noticed
   you were gone.

03:59.073 --> 04:00.272
             Cloris.

04:00.274 --> 04:02.040
       Rosie.
                     Cloris.

04:02.042 --> 04:03.508
        Rosie.

04:03.510 --> 04:04.876
                   Cloris.

04:04.878 --> 04:05.911
              Hmm?

04:05.913 --> 04:07.112
               Hmm?

04:07.114 --> 04:09.915
          Bye, Cloris!

04:09.917 --> 04:11.750
     Jeff, dear,
   your friend has

04:11.752 --> 04:15.220
an unfortunate amount of space
 between his teeth.

04:15.222 --> 04:17.189
              Mom.
           Oh, that's all right.

04:17.190 --> 04:20.225
      My mom says that I'll grow
             into them in time.

04:20.226 --> 04:22.561
   That's nice of
your mom to say that.

04:22.563 --> 04:26.565
Tell Granny more about your
alphabetized leaf collection.

04:26.567 --> 04:29.368
            Well, I started with
          an "F" for "Fig" leaf,

04:29.370 --> 04:31.737
         [ Groans ]
    then "G" for "Grape" leaf...

04:31.739 --> 04:32.638
            Mnh-mnh.

04:32.640 --> 04:35.073
                   I want
          my rotisserie chicken!

04:35.075 --> 04:36.441
     No, Cloris.

04:36.443 --> 04:38.377
Why, you know that's
too much salt for you.

04:38.379 --> 04:40.312
      -Yes, it's always --
          -Oh, I know.

04:40.314 --> 04:42.781
  [ Indistinct conversations ]

04:42.783 --> 04:44.983
   Hi, Cloris!
                       Aaaah!

04:44.985 --> 04:46.318
        So...

04:46.320 --> 04:48.654
         [ Screaming continues ]
So I was thinking --

04:48.656 --> 04:51.657
             [ Panting ] You --
     You trying to kill me, boy?

04:51.659 --> 04:54.493
  So, I was eating
with Jeff and his grandma,

04:54.495 --> 04:56.595
  but they're being
    so boring --

04:56.597 --> 04:58.964
             That old salad tong
              is always boring.

04:58.966 --> 05:00.332
      Everything here is boring.

05:00.334 --> 05:01.833
              Especially lunch!

05:01.835 --> 05:03.001
      [ Gasps ]

05:03.003 --> 05:04.836
              Ooh.
   It looks like you slipped.

05:04.838 --> 05:06.171
                    See?

05:06.173 --> 05:07.406
Whaaaa! At my school,

05:07.408 --> 05:09.741
    lunch is like
the best part of the day.

05:09.743 --> 05:11.576
 This place is a lot
   like my school.

05:11.578 --> 05:14.780
  Chicken nuggets,
and you got yearbooks, nap time.

05:14.782 --> 05:17.516
  And the teachers
are all like my mom's age.

05:17.518 --> 05:20.152
        Everyone here treats you
                like a child!

05:20.154 --> 05:22.254
  I'll show you how
 to many lunch fun.

05:22.256 --> 05:23.255
        Don't touch me, heathen.

05:23.257 --> 05:24.256
    Come on!
                        No!

05:24.258 --> 05:25.357
   Come on!
                          No.

05:25.359 --> 05:27.025
                 Don't touch me.
I'm gonna do it.

05:27.027 --> 05:28.760
    [ Chuckles ]
                      No! No!

05:28.762 --> 05:29.594
     I got you.
                          No!

05:29.596 --> 05:31.663
             What --
Elanor Josephine,

05:31.665 --> 05:34.933
    a Nosey Nancy
makes a no-good house wife.

05:34.935 --> 05:37.602
        How come you want
        to alone so bad?

05:37.604 --> 05:40.038
             'Cause I don't want
                 to be here.

05:40.040 --> 05:43.008
             Just waiting to...
                  you know.

05:43.010 --> 05:44.376
         [ Bell tolls ]

05:44.378 --> 05:46.144
   Bathroom?
                   [ Grumbles ]

05:46.146 --> 05:47.846
Anyways, want to pretend
  like it's recess?

05:47.848 --> 05:51.350
              Recess never came
          for old bones like me.

05:51.352 --> 05:53.452
     I'm hearing
 what you're saying,

05:53.454 --> 05:58.056
but I think we're about to have
a little recess right now.

05:58.058 --> 06:01.159
   Follow my lead.

06:01.161 --> 06:02.327
               [ Gasps ] Huh?

06:02.329 --> 06:04.629
      Hot dog!
    A food fight!

06:04.631 --> 06:06.231
     [ Laughs ]

06:06.233 --> 06:09.067
     [ Grunting, shouting ]

06:09.903 --> 06:11.837
   They've got us surrounded!
       They're everywhere!

06:11.839 --> 06:13.505
      They're in the trees!
         Watch your six!

06:13.507 --> 06:14.906
  We got to get you
   somewhere safe!

06:14.908 --> 06:17.576
      Let go! You're the one who
        started all this ruckus!

06:17.578 --> 06:21.179
 We can to the park
and then have a real recess.

06:21.181 --> 06:22.581
                     ��

06:22.583 --> 06:24.483
        Ahh.

06:25.753 --> 06:27.953
        [ Bees buzzing ]

06:34.661 --> 06:35.761
     [ Groans ]

06:35.763 --> 06:37.429
                 [ Laughs ]

06:37.431 --> 06:41.333
     Use your pool scepters
      and stir that water.

06:41.335 --> 06:44.069
 Mmm, like a giant cosmic stew.

06:44.071 --> 06:45.103
           You, me...

06:45.105 --> 06:46.571
              Elanor Josephine,

06:46.573 --> 06:49.207
             you stir that water
       with a little more gusto.

06:49.209 --> 06:50.442
     [ Growls ]

06:50.444 --> 06:52.244
   Now raise those arms high!

06:52.246 --> 06:55.180
We call this the war cry stance.

06:55.182 --> 06:57.282
                Higher, dear.
                   Higher!

06:57.284 --> 06:58.417
          Get those arms higher!

06:58.419 --> 07:00.452
            Ohhhhhh!
          Enough, Mom!

07:00.454 --> 07:02.621
    Can you stop controlling
   everyone for just a second.

07:02.623 --> 07:04.556
       People get to chose
     their own way of life,

07:04.558 --> 07:06.191
         and that's what
        makes them happy.

07:06.193 --> 07:07.192
                    Jeff:
              Are you two done?

07:07.194 --> 07:08.627
              -Huh?
              -Huh?

07:08.629 --> 07:11.129
   Grandma Day is my favorite
      holiday of the month,

07:11.131 --> 07:12.764
   but you two are ruining it!

07:12.766 --> 07:16.134
    Grandma Rose, you need to
 respect that mom isn't like us.

07:16.136 --> 07:20.105
   She's messy, inconsistent,
   but that's just who she is.

07:20.107 --> 07:23.308
      And Mom, Grandma Rose
      might be overbearing,

07:23.310 --> 07:25.410
       but she's choosing
       her own path, too.

07:25.412 --> 07:28.079
        I love you both,
 but if you don't let me finish

07:28.081 --> 07:31.216
  my artistic stretching class,
       I'm really gonna --

07:31.218 --> 07:33.952
  I'm gonna just blow my stack!

07:33.954 --> 07:35.487
                Oh, Jeffrey.

07:35.489 --> 07:37.823
              I'm sorry, dear.

07:37.825 --> 07:39.424
    Sorry, Jeff.

07:39.426 --> 07:41.460
     Sorry, Mom.

07:41.462 --> 07:44.162
            [ Sighs ]
       That was beautiful.

07:44.164 --> 07:45.430
     What a beautiful stew.

07:45.432 --> 07:47.432
             Do any of you know
            where Clarence went?

07:47.434 --> 07:50.335
Malessica told Courtlin that
Kimby liked Sumo, and --

07:50.337 --> 07:51.503
  Oh, and Belson --

07:51.505 --> 07:52.971
   Oh, you'd like
    Belson a lot.

07:52.973 --> 07:54.005
                 I doubt it.

07:54.007 --> 07:55.173
                    Hmm.

07:55.175 --> 07:57.275
               Let's go back.
            I got to feed Sassy.

07:57.277 --> 08:01.012
        Uhhh.
Okay, well, I guess it's --

08:01.014 --> 08:02.848
                  No wait.

08:02.850 --> 08:04.349
                  This way?

08:04.351 --> 08:05.584
 You're lost, dummy?

08:05.586 --> 08:06.351
        Ugh.

08:06.353 --> 08:08.153
               Just follow me.

08:08.155 --> 08:10.455
      Uh, I can
  keep pushing you!

08:10.457 --> 08:12.457
                  I'm fine.

08:12.459 --> 08:14.025
      You sure
you don't need help?

08:14.027 --> 08:16.862
      Listen. I've taken care of
           myself all this time.

08:16.864 --> 08:20.265
   So maybe you should mind your
own business from now on, sonny.

08:20.267 --> 08:24.769
             This isn't recess,
             and I'm not a kid.

08:24.771 --> 08:26.171
      [ Sighs ]

08:26.173 --> 08:29.708
       I guess
I'll leave you alone.

08:29.710 --> 08:32.677
             Uh, kid, it's just
        that I've been on my own

08:32.679 --> 08:34.880
         for so long, and, uh --

08:34.881 --> 08:36.313
       Cloris!

08:36.316 --> 08:39.351
        Cloris!

08:39.352 --> 08:42.053
      Cloris!

08:42.054 --> 08:43.221
  [ Gasps ] Oh, no!

08:43.222 --> 08:45.724
     [ Panting ]
Cloris, are you okay?

08:45.726 --> 08:46.725
                    Yeah.

08:46.727 --> 08:50.061
                   I guess
           you can push me home.

08:50.063 --> 08:52.030
    Cloris! Look!

08:54.167 --> 08:55.700
                  By Jove.

08:55.702 --> 08:58.870
             Oh, I never thought
       I'd see this place again.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.038
When I was young, I --

09:00.040 --> 09:03.008
I buried some treasure
under that tree over there.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.911
              What? Treasure?!

09:05.913 --> 09:07.078
            [ Grunts ] Treasure!

09:07.080 --> 09:08.880
             Treasure, treasure,
             treasure, treasure!

09:08.882 --> 09:10.582
  I had to bury it
    underground.

09:10.584 --> 09:13.518
 So that darn Rosie
  wouldn't find it.

09:13.520 --> 09:15.353
             I found something!

09:15.355 --> 09:16.588
     We're rich!

09:16.590 --> 09:19.524
               Bring it here.

09:19.526 --> 09:21.459
                 [ Coughs ]

09:24.264 --> 09:25.897
        Whoa.

09:25.899 --> 09:26.932
                What is that?

09:26.934 --> 09:29.334
                 Just paper?

09:29.336 --> 09:31.503
        My greatest work.

09:31.505 --> 09:35.840
                   "Rosie
              is a Slugburger?"

09:35.842 --> 09:38.843
               She really was
             such a slugburger.

09:38.845 --> 09:39.945
                 [ Laughs ]

09:39.947 --> 09:42.647
  Oh. [ Chuckles ]

09:44.117 --> 09:45.183
     Slugburger.

09:45.185 --> 09:46.418
        [ Coins jingle ]

09:46.420 --> 09:48.687
   Hey, you jerk!
 We're not homeless!

09:48.689 --> 09:52.090
  No one wants your dirty money,
       you chicken-legged scamp!

09:52.092 --> 09:53.224
    [ Chuckles ]

09:53.226 --> 09:54.960
You love chicken legs!

09:54.962 --> 09:55.794
                 [ Laughs ]

09:55.796 --> 09:57.596
              Go suck on a egg
                if you want.

09:57.598 --> 09:59.130
 Yeah! Go to the --

09:59.132 --> 10:01.132
Go live on the moon!

10:01.134 --> 10:02.701
   [ Chuckles ]
                      [ Laughs ]

10:02.703 --> 10:05.303
                  Good one.
     Hey, I think there's enough

10:05.305 --> 10:07.472
        for a rotisserie chicken
                  in here.

10:07.474 --> 10:09.774
                 [ Laughs ]

10:11.578 --> 10:12.777
 Oh, well, thank --

10:12.779 --> 10:14.145
     Hi. Well --
 [ Exhales sharply ]

10:14.147 --> 10:16.114
 There you two are.

10:16.116 --> 10:17.616
          � Oh, Rosie �

10:17.618 --> 10:20.585
� She is a slugburger �

10:20.587 --> 10:22.487
� She eats worms for dinner �

10:22.489 --> 10:23.488
                [ Chuckles ]

10:23.490 --> 10:25.824
� She's a slugburger-ger �

10:25.826 --> 10:26.758
                That's gross.

10:26.760 --> 10:28.493
Oh, hey. It's Clarence.
    There he is.

10:28.495 --> 10:31.730
           � Oh, Rosie,
     she is a simple rube �
                   [ Chuckles ]

10:31.732 --> 10:33.498
           Oh, Cloris!
      I thought I told her

10:33.500 --> 10:35.233
          never to play
      that darn tune again.

10:35.235 --> 10:36.635
     � She's a slugburger �
      Hey, stop that song.

10:36.637 --> 10:38.837
           Stop that!
      I'm not a slugburger!

10:38.839 --> 10:41.840
        � She says she'll
      always be your friend �
Jeffrey! You get your
friend out of there!

10:41.842 --> 10:43.308
       � Through the thick
     and through the thin �

10:43.310 --> 10:44.509
                [ Chuckles ]
           This is a funny song.

10:44.511 --> 10:46.511
         � But when push
        comes to shove �

10:46.513 --> 10:48.980
         � She'll snitch
        and wear a grin �

10:48.982 --> 10:51.182
                That's not nice.
          � Oh, Rosie �

10:51.184 --> 10:53.985
     � She is a slugburger �

10:53.987 --> 10:56.187
  � She eats worms for dinner �

10:56.189 --> 10:57.522
                  Oh, yuck.

10:57.524 --> 11:00.025
     � She's a slugburger �
   [ Meows ]

11:00.027 --> 11:03.061
                    [ Chuckles ]
      And that's the truth.

11:04.264 --> 11:07.365
        � Early to bed �

11:07.367 --> 11:11.269
        � Early to rise �

11:11.271 --> 11:14.739
       � Picking my nose �

11:26.887 --> 11:27.952
                  Hyuh! Oh!

11:27.954 --> 11:28.987
              Hyuh!

11:28.989 --> 11:31.389
           Hey, Sumo.
       What are you doing?

11:31.391 --> 11:33.658
 Helping my dad fix
his crawdaddy cages.

11:33.660 --> 11:36.461
              Whoa.
       What's a crawdaddy?

11:36.463 --> 11:38.329
  They're like bugs
that live underwater.

11:38.331 --> 11:39.564
 Taste good, though.

11:39.566 --> 11:42.500
                  Actually,
         it's a type of crusta--

11:42.502 --> 11:44.836
            Hey, Mel. Thanks for
        watching Clarence today.

11:44.838 --> 11:46.304
Put your hand right there
       for me.

11:46.306 --> 11:47.839
                  Oh, yeah.
                    Sure.

11:47.841 --> 11:49.340
                    Aah!

11:49.342 --> 11:51.209
Tried getting the boy
     to help me,

11:51.211 --> 11:52.677
    but you know
    how kids are.

11:52.679 --> 11:55.046
They got to have their own
way of doing things.

11:55.048 --> 11:57.182
                [ Chuckles ]

11:57.184 --> 11:58.883
    [ Chuckles ]

11:58.885 --> 12:00.018
       Hello.

12:00.020 --> 12:01.653
       Look at their faces
          in the cage.

12:01.655 --> 12:03.521
                  Oh, yeah.
                    Kids.

12:03.523 --> 12:05.423
                   So, um,
           what is this, anyway?

12:05.425 --> 12:07.859
    Crawdad trap.
   My own design.

12:07.861 --> 12:11.262
              Whoa.
Sumo, are these your dad's toys?

12:11.264 --> 12:13.431
              That right there
                ain't no toy.

12:13.433 --> 12:15.200
         It's for catching fish.

12:15.202 --> 12:16.735
        Yeah,
 I never done that.

12:16.737 --> 12:19.404
My mom usually gets fish sticks
  at Food Nephews.

12:19.406 --> 12:21.439
     Aah! Owie.

12:21.441 --> 12:23.241
            You never
     took your boy fishin'?

12:23.243 --> 12:25.210
               Oh, well, uh...

12:25.212 --> 12:27.078
                  You know.
                 [ Sniffs ]

12:27.080 --> 12:29.013
                    Ugh.

12:29.015 --> 12:30.782
   I went fishing
     last week.

12:30.784 --> 12:32.383
      Actually,
 it wasn't fishing.

12:32.385 --> 12:34.085
It was a nature walk
     in Sedona.

12:34.087 --> 12:36.788
     At the end,
 my mom got me this!

12:36.790 --> 12:39.691
A multipurpose Gator tool!

12:39.693 --> 12:41.593
It's got a toothpick.

12:41.595 --> 12:44.562
     Fishing sounds so fun.

12:44.564 --> 12:47.599
Sumo! Go get the fishin' poles
 out of the garage.

12:47.601 --> 12:49.567
We're takin' these boys
    to the river

12:49.569 --> 12:52.170
  and showing them
what fishing's all about.

12:55.475 --> 12:58.076
           [ Sniffs ]
          Ahh. No bugs.

12:58.078 --> 13:00.545
    But, Mother,
I do not wish to marry him.

13:00.547 --> 13:01.980
               Silence, missy!

13:01.982 --> 13:04.282
         [ Both laugh ]

13:04.284 --> 13:05.450
                  Um, wait.

13:05.452 --> 13:06.918
       Um, logistically -- Um...

13:06.920 --> 13:09.654
All right, now, if we split up,
we'll catch more fish.

13:09.656 --> 13:11.823
          Hey, Mel, are we gonna
         maybe eat or something?

13:11.825 --> 13:13.725
       We eat
 whatever we catch.
                       [ Gasps ]

13:13.727 --> 13:15.927
 Chad, you take Sumo
 and the other one.

13:15.929 --> 13:17.095
           Other one?

13:17.097 --> 13:19.764
Clarence, since this is
your first time out there,

13:19.766 --> 13:22.133
      you'll be
in good hands with me.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.269
                That's fine.

13:24.271 --> 13:25.470
                    Sure.

13:25.472 --> 13:27.105
         Here. I got it.
              Whoa.

13:27.107 --> 13:30.241
  Uh, Chad. This boat is small,
         and you're not.

13:30.243 --> 13:33.244
Oh, and Sumo, just try to
keep the boat from sinking.

13:33.246 --> 13:35.780
     What? I can whip these guys
                 into shape.

13:35.782 --> 13:38.082
     [ Laughs ]
How about a little wager?

13:38.084 --> 13:41.953
If I catch more fish,
you have to wash all my dogs.

13:41.955 --> 13:43.454
                 [ Scoffs ]
     Well, it's not gonna happen

13:43.456 --> 13:46.291
 'cause if I win, I get to trash
            sled around the yard

13:46.293 --> 13:47.458
             as long as I want!

13:47.460 --> 13:49.627
     All right.
You got yourself a deal.

13:49.629 --> 13:51.462
             -Deal.
              -Hmm.

13:51.464 --> 13:52.964
         Mm.

13:52.966 --> 13:54.499
Bye!

13:54.501 --> 13:55.800
Have fun!

13:55.802 --> 13:57.802
             Come on, Clarence.

13:57.804 --> 13:59.671
   All right, now,
first thing's first.

13:59.673 --> 14:01.673
         [ Blowing raspberries ]

14:10.317 --> 14:13.384
         Okay, everyone take out
    your fishing poles, I think,

14:13.386 --> 14:16.988
        and, uh, this twine here
     is what the fish will grab.

14:16.990 --> 14:20.658
                   Ugh.
I packed some fresh granola
if anybody wants any.

14:20.660 --> 14:22.227
             Um, hold on. Wait.

14:22.229 --> 14:24.829
       Hey, you sure there
  are crawdaddies around here?

14:24.831 --> 14:26.497
            No rocks
      for them hide under.

14:26.499 --> 14:28.132
        No seaweed stuff
        for them to eat.

14:28.134 --> 14:30.835
Actually, seaweed is in
saltwater and algae --

14:30.837 --> 14:33.304
           [ Groans ]
      All right, listen up.

14:33.306 --> 14:36.474
     We're looking for bass
     and crawdaddies today.

14:36.476 --> 14:39.210
      Anything smaller than
   this stick, throw it back.

14:39.212 --> 14:41.980
 We are filling this whole boat
           with fish.

14:41.982 --> 14:44.315
                [ Chuckles ]
           That's a lot of fish!

14:44.317 --> 14:47.886
       [ Pan flute plays ]

14:47.888 --> 14:49.787
                     Hm.

14:52.025 --> 14:53.725
 So, what's it like
 being Sumo's daddy?

14:53.727 --> 14:56.794
                    Shh.
               We're fishing.

14:57.864 --> 14:59.530
What happened to your hand?

14:59.532 --> 15:00.732
               Dog nicked it.

15:00.734 --> 15:02.567
     Do you miss
  your other kids?

15:02.569 --> 15:04.869
             -What?
  -'Cause they're all at home.

15:04.871 --> 15:06.604
 Are you gonna keep
   all your kids?

15:06.606 --> 15:08.172
         What are you talking --

15:08.174 --> 15:10.241
I brought some sammiches
    for the fish

15:10.243 --> 15:11.776
in case they get hungry.

15:11.778 --> 15:14.045
                 [ Groans ]

15:14.047 --> 15:17.615
  First, you got to really get
 down in there and look around.

15:17.617 --> 15:21.753
          [ Gurgling ]

15:21.755 --> 15:23.788
           You got to
       show them your face

15:23.790 --> 15:25.223
     before they'll let you
           catch 'em.

15:25.225 --> 15:26.224
           Who's next?

15:26.226 --> 15:27.725
   Uhh...
                    Uh...

15:27.727 --> 15:29.060
         -Come on, Chad.
             -What?

15:29.062 --> 15:30.528
                  Let's go.
                 You first.

15:30.530 --> 15:31.562
     -[ Chuckles nervously ]
            -Come on.

15:31.564 --> 15:33.264
     I don't --
      No, I --

15:33.266 --> 15:34.432
        Oh, geez, you're strong.

15:34.434 --> 15:36.401
             Ow, ow.

15:36.403 --> 15:39.570
    [ Chuckles ]

15:39.572 --> 15:41.773
                 [ Panting ]

15:41.775 --> 15:44.876
        How about we use
        the fishing gear

15:44.878 --> 15:47.278
         that's actually
        made for fishing?

15:47.280 --> 15:48.146
               Oh.

15:48.148 --> 15:49.981
        [ Bird squawks ]
          Aah! Ow! Ow!

15:49.983 --> 15:52.216
       That's right, Jeff!
       Show it your face!

15:52.218 --> 15:53.484
           [ Laughs ]

15:53.486 --> 15:55.320
                  [ Gasps ]
                 A sandwich!

15:56.957 --> 15:58.256
                    Aww.

15:58.258 --> 16:00.558
       Mel: All right, Clarence,
         now, to cast your line,

16:00.560 --> 16:03.094
       you got to pull her back,
             thumb on the spool,

16:03.096 --> 16:05.229
       then gently let her loose
                  like so.

16:05.231 --> 16:07.498
                     ��

16:07.500 --> 16:09.133
                    See?
               Pretty simple.

16:09.135 --> 16:11.669
                    Here.
             Now give it a try.

16:11.671 --> 16:13.104
     [ Groans ]

16:13.106 --> 16:14.339
        Hyah!

16:15.742 --> 16:17.508
                That's okay.

16:17.510 --> 16:19.110
           We'll try that again.

16:19.112 --> 16:20.945
        Hyah!

16:20.947 --> 16:22.180
              Now, you just --

16:22.182 --> 16:24.248
                 You gave it
        a little too much there.

16:24.250 --> 16:25.750
               Try that again.

16:25.752 --> 16:27.652
        Hyah.

16:27.654 --> 16:32.623
    Okay. Now, you did something
      right and something wrong.

16:32.625 --> 16:33.925
    [ Gurgling ]

16:33.927 --> 16:35.626
 Here fishy, fishy.

16:35.628 --> 16:37.528
  Come and get me!
    [ Grunting ]

16:37.530 --> 16:38.997
        Well, looks like
        you've got things

16:38.999 --> 16:41.966
      pretty under control
           over here.

16:41.968 --> 16:44.435
              Hey.
 Everything okay over here, bud?

16:44.437 --> 16:47.438
   [ Chuckles ] I'm still making
        a few extra adjustments.

16:47.440 --> 16:50.641
No reward goes to the unprepared
            angler, as they say.

16:50.643 --> 16:52.210
                 [ Giggles ]

16:53.146 --> 16:56.180
Okay, well, you know, Jeff,
     I was just checking in.

16:56.182 --> 16:59.317
   Things we don't know about
  our children's friends, huh?

16:59.319 --> 17:00.485
              Wow.

17:00.487 --> 17:02.520
               Mr. Sumo's dad!

17:02.522 --> 17:03.521
                  I did it!

17:03.523 --> 17:05.022
        Hey.
   Great job, kid.

17:05.025 --> 17:06.958
        I --
 What in the world.

17:06.960 --> 17:09.993
That's a little far,
      Clarence.

17:09.996 --> 17:12.696
Why don't you reel 'er back in
   and try again?

17:12.699 --> 17:15.532
                [ Chuckles ]

17:15.535 --> 17:17.835
        -Oh, no. No, no.
  -Come on. Dunk your head in!

17:17.837 --> 17:19.670
               No, Sumo! Stop.

17:19.672 --> 17:21.204
                 Why are you
               such a lunatic?

17:21.207 --> 17:23.174
      Come on!
You've never even been fishin'!

17:23.175 --> 17:25.175
            Uh, hey.
         Come on, guys.

17:25.178 --> 17:26.411
              Huh?

17:26.413 --> 17:27.412
              Aah!

17:27.414 --> 17:29.714
          [ Screaming ]

17:29.716 --> 17:31.149
        Aah!

17:31.151 --> 17:33.151
            The fish!
   They're trying to eat him!

17:33.153 --> 17:34.318
      Oh, boy.

17:34.320 --> 17:36.154
     Looks like
you caught a biggin'.

17:36.156 --> 17:39.190
                 [ Groans ]
              Almost...got it.

17:39.192 --> 17:40.591
                [ Groaning ]
              Come here, fish.

17:40.593 --> 17:41.859
                 You're just
               being stubborn.

17:41.861 --> 17:45.329
            [ Rip! ]
           Chad: Aah!

17:45.331 --> 17:48.032
      Whoo-wee!
Let's see what we got here.

17:48.034 --> 17:51.102
      I think it might have been
      a baby shark or something.

17:52.105 --> 17:53.237
        Hmm.

17:53.239 --> 17:56.007
Must be some old clump
of bear fur or something.

17:56.009 --> 17:57.775
          [ Screaming ]

17:57.777 --> 17:58.910
        Chad!

17:58.912 --> 18:00.878
                    A-ha!
       I'll use my tape measure.

18:00.880 --> 18:02.046
           Grab onto this, Chad!

18:02.048 --> 18:05.049
     [ Screaming continues ]

18:05.051 --> 18:07.785
Put that stupid toy away,
        Jeff!

18:07.787 --> 18:10.588
  Chad, grab this!

18:10.590 --> 18:12.490
            [ Thud ]
              Aah!

18:15.895 --> 18:17.862
           [ Panting ]

18:17.864 --> 18:19.030
                  [ Sighs ]

18:19.032 --> 18:21.399
                  Oh, man.
           That was a close one.

18:21.401 --> 18:22.433
                Thanks, guys.

18:22.435 --> 18:24.435
           -[ Gasps ]
     -Especially you, Sumo.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.237
                    What?
  Is there something on my face?

18:26.239 --> 18:27.105
                    Aah!

18:27.107 --> 18:29.273
            [ Sighs ] [ Groans ]
                [ Chuckles ]

18:29.275 --> 18:31.709
      I guess I haven't showered
            in a few days, so...

18:31.711 --> 18:32.710
      [ Gags ]

18:32.712 --> 18:33.978
               Musk of a man.

18:33.980 --> 18:36.447
           [ Ticking ]

18:41.121 --> 18:43.221
               Oh.

18:44.591 --> 18:45.923
  Mel: Well, shoot.

18:45.925 --> 18:48.259
Somebody must've already
fished this area today.

18:48.261 --> 18:50.261
     That's it.
 Let's try upstream.

18:50.263 --> 18:52.797
              Maybe it's 'cause
         the food is too boring.

18:52.799 --> 18:54.098
             Got to spice it up.

18:54.100 --> 18:56.400
             My mom says that --

18:56.402 --> 18:58.836
               that every meal
     should be like a rainbow --

18:58.838 --> 19:00.271
             with all the colors
                put together.

19:00.273 --> 19:02.273
                So, you know,
    it's got all the good stuff.

19:02.275 --> 19:06.010
I have a set method.
  It always works.

19:06.012 --> 19:08.312
               I guess always,
               except for now,

19:08.314 --> 19:11.949
  and you're gonna lose that bet
        to Sumo, who's your son.

19:11.951 --> 19:13.284
     [ Groans ]

19:13.286 --> 19:14.919
                     ��

19:14.921 --> 19:18.623
                Some of that.

19:18.625 --> 19:20.291
                    Hyah!

19:20.293 --> 19:21.292
      Oh, wait!

19:21.294 --> 19:23.161
                    Now,
          hold on just a minute.

19:23.163 --> 19:25.963
             What are you doing?
   That's not bait for crawdads.

19:25.965 --> 19:28.166
                Certain fish
             need certain bait.

19:28.168 --> 19:30.067
              Now, a crawdad --

19:32.705 --> 19:34.172
           Well, I'll be darned.

19:34.174 --> 19:35.606
  [ Chuckles ] See?

19:35.608 --> 19:37.141
Crawdads need rainbows, too.

19:37.143 --> 19:39.477
               Hmm. Go ahead.
          Do it again, Clarence.

19:39.479 --> 19:40.645
        Okay.

19:40.647 --> 19:42.813
      -One more! One more!
     -[ Muffled screaming ]

19:42.815 --> 19:44.448
          One last one!

19:44.450 --> 19:47.485
     [ Laughs ]

19:47.487 --> 19:50.555
                     ��

19:57.497 --> 19:58.696
              Aah!

19:58.698 --> 19:59.897
        [ Laughing ] Oh!

19:59.899 --> 20:02.400
        [ Both laughing ]

20:04.404 --> 20:07.071
        [ Both laughing ]

20:07.073 --> 20:09.640
             -Yeah!
           -Oh, Sumo.

20:09.642 --> 20:12.743
                     ��

20:15.682 --> 20:17.415
         [ Gasps ] Wow.

20:17.417 --> 20:20.384
                    Hmm.

20:20.386 --> 20:21.986
                [ Chuckles ]

20:21.988 --> 20:23.854
                 [ Grunts ]

20:23.856 --> 20:26.624
          [ Laughter ]

20:28.094 --> 20:29.393
     [ Growls ]

20:29.395 --> 20:30.661
          [ Screaming ]

20:30.663 --> 20:32.863
          -Stop! Stop!
  -Give him whatever he wants!

20:32.865 --> 20:34.699
     [ Screaming continues ]

20:34.701 --> 20:36.200
 He's gonna get us!

20:36.202 --> 20:38.703
        Sumo: Give him the fish!
             Give him the fish!

20:38.705 --> 20:40.771
                Oh, no! Aah!

20:40.773 --> 20:42.039
       Oh, my!

20:42.041 --> 20:44.875
            [ Sighs ]
 I got to hand it to you, Sumo.

20:44.877 --> 20:46.177
                You're a lot
               like your dad.

20:46.179 --> 20:49.113
                You scare me,
            but you get results.

20:53.419 --> 20:55.119
         [ Both slurp ]

20:55.121 --> 20:56.454
          [ Both sigh ]

20:56.456 --> 20:57.521
    [ Chuckles ]

20:57.523 --> 20:59.457
 You're a good kid,
      Clarence.

20:59.459 --> 21:02.727
I'm glad your Sumo's
little friend or whatever.

21:02.729 --> 21:04.362
         Clarence: Bye, friends.

21:04.364 --> 21:06.897
      Hope you liked your lunch!

21:06.899 --> 21:09.600
   What are you --
      [ Sighs ]

21:09.602 --> 21:11.135
      Oh, man.

21:11.137 --> 21:13.537
     [ Grunts ]

21:13.539 --> 21:15.206
                  Hey, man.

21:15.208 --> 21:16.607
                 I just want
              to say thank you,

21:16.609 --> 21:18.576
 you know, for bring me out here
               with the boys.

21:18.578 --> 21:20.444
      It was just great to just,
                  you know,

21:20.446 --> 21:22.113
              get on the water,
                  you know?

21:22.115 --> 21:23.914
        Uh, you bet, man.

21:23.916 --> 21:26.417
              Aah!
   What happened to your head?

21:26.419 --> 21:28.586
 [ Laughs ]

21:28.588 --> 21:29.487
              D'oh!

21:29.489 --> 21:31.055
                  So, Dad,
             how about the bet?

21:31.057 --> 21:32.223
                How many fish
               did you catch?

21:32.225 --> 21:33.758
    Oh, well, actually, we --

21:33.760 --> 21:36.093
Well, no fish for us.

21:36.095 --> 21:37.995
       I guess
it just wasn't our day.

21:37.997 --> 21:39.664
                    Wait.
               I won the bet!

21:39.666 --> 21:40.965
                I won! I won!

21:40.967 --> 21:43.234
          [ Chuckles ]
       That's right, Sumo.

21:43.236 --> 21:46.470
       Well, I guess it's
     garbage-sledding time.

21:46.472 --> 21:48.506
        [ Sumo laughing ]

21:48.508 --> 21:49.807
        [ Dogs barking ]

21:49.809 --> 21:51.142
          [ Chuckles ]

21:51.144 --> 21:55.146
    He's still gonna have to
       wash all them dogs.

21:56.916 --> 21:58.749
        � Early to bed �

22:00.286 --> 22:02.420
        � Early to rise �

22:03.923 --> 22:06.824
       � Picking my nose �
